--- 
// /home/r_/projects/jeremysayers/src/pages/education.astro
import NewsletterSignup from '../components/NewsletterSignup.astro';
import PageIntro from '../components/PageIntro.astro';
import SectionHeading from '../components/SectionHeading.astro';
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Education & Community | Jeremy Sayers"
  description="Jeremy Sayers on teaching, school leadership, family partnership, STEM, robotics, and the school-community connections that help students thrive."
  showSitewideSignup={false}
>
  <PageIntro
    title="Education & Community"
    description="Jeremy Sayers brings together classroom experience, educational leadership, STEM advocacy, and a strong belief that schools are strongest when educators and families work together."
  />

  <section class="section-band section-band--paper">
    <div class="shell education-grid">
      <div class="stack">
        <SectionHeading
          eyebrow="Teaching and Leadership"
          title="Classroom experience, leadership, and a practical commitment to student opportunity."
        />
        <p>
          Jeremy’s work in education is shaped by years of experience teaching elementary students across grade levels
          kindergarten through fifth grade. That range brings a broader understanding of how students grow, where they
          need support, and what meaningful learning looks like at different stages.
        </p>
        <p>
          His approach to education is practical and student-centered. Strong instruction, high expectations, and real
          opportunities matter. The goal is not only academic growth, but helping students build confidence, curiosity,
          and a sense of possibility about what they can do.
        </p>
      </div>
      <aside class="pullquote-card">
        <h3>Strong schools are built through teaching, trust, and meaningful partnership with families.</h3>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-band section-band--paper">
    <div class="shell">
      <SectionHeading
        eyebrow="Family Partnership"
        title="The best educational environments are partnerships with families."
      />
      <p class="education-community__lead">
        Lasting school success does not come from educators working alone. It grows when schools and families build
        trust, communicate clearly, and participate together in the life of the school.
      </p>
      <p class="education-community__lead">
        Jeremy believes family partnership should be treated as an essential part of student success. When families are
        welcomed into meaningful roles, school communities become stronger, more connected, and better able to support
        children.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-band section-band--slate">
    <div class="shell">
      <SectionHeading
        eyebrow="STEM and Hands-On Learning"
        title="Students need opportunities to build, create, problem-solve, and discover what they can do."
      />
      <div class="about-story-grid">
        <article class="panel">
          <p>
            Jeremy has a strong interest in STEM, robotics, innovation, and applied learning. Hands-on experiences can
            change how students see themselves and help them develop persistence, teamwork, and confidence.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="panel">
          <p>
            Robotics, engineering, making, and creative problem-solving give students real opportunities to test ideas,
            recover from setbacks, and discover strengths they may not have seen in themselves before. VEX Robotics and
            related programs also show the value of parent involvement, encouragement, and shared investment in student
            growth.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-band section-band--accent">
    <div class="shell">
      <SectionHeading
        eyebrow="Community Involvement"
        title="School communities grow stronger when people show up, participate, and contribute."
      />
      <p class="education-community__lead">
        A healthy school community is built through steady involvement. Events, committees, arts programs, and school
        activities all help create the trust and shared responsibility that students benefit from most.
      </p>
      <p class="education-community__lead">
        That belief is reflected in Jeremy’s own family life as well. Parents have been very involved in VEX
        Robotics, and Mrs. Sayers has been actively involved in Adventures in Art, school events, and school
        committees. It reflects a larger belief that schools are stronger when families, educators, and community
        members all have a real place in the work.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-band section-band--warm">
    <div class="shell">
      <SectionHeading
        eyebrow="Education and Credentials"
        title="A concise view of Jeremy’s academic and professional background."
      />
      <article class="panel credential-panel">
        <ul class="credential-list">
          <li>El Camino College — A.A. History, A.S. Computer Information Systems</li>
          <li>UC San Diego — B.A. History</li>
          <li>National University — Master’s in Education, Teaching Credential</li>
          <li>USC — Administrative Credential</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="credential-panel__note">
          This background reflects Jeremy’s long-standing interest in learning, leadership, technology, and the
          systems that help schools serve students and families well.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-band section-band--paper">
    <div class="shell stay-grid">
      <div class="stack">
        <SectionHeading
          eyebrow="Stay Connected"
          title="Get updates on education, school-community ideas, and practical work."
          text="If you want to follow Jeremy’s education work, projects, and future updates, this is the best place to stay in touch."
        />
        <p>
          The updates list is designed for occasional, useful communication about schools, hands-on learning, family
          partnership, and community-minded work.
        </p>
      </div>
      <NewsletterSignup
        title="Stay Connected"
        text="Join for occasional updates on education, family partnership, STEM, robotics, and practical projects."
        sourceContext="education-community-page"
      />
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
